# scripts/jre.env
#
# Single source of truth for the jlink-bundled Java runtime: exact Temurin build +
# module list. Sourced by build-jre.sh / check-jre-modules.sh (plain `source`, bash)
# and parsed by build-jre.ps1 (regex over KEY="value" lines) — keep the syntax to
# simple assignments and '#' comments so both readers work.
#
# See docs/design/01-architecture.md §3 (Java runtime bundling) and
# docs/adr/003-tauri-jlink-resources.md.

# Exact Temurin build pinned on every platform (dev JDK, Adoptium download, CI) —
# per CLAUDE.md "Pinned versions" table: "Same patch bundled on all platforms."
# Format matches the Adoptium API version-endpoint path segment exactly.
TEMURIN_VERSION="jdk-21.0.11+10"

# jlink module list: docs/design/01-architecture.md §3's curated list, PLUS
# java.logging (embedded Tomcat JULI — see docs/adr/003-tauri-jlink-resources.md,
# a deliberate red-team catch, NOT present in the original design-doc list), PLUS
# whatever scripts/check-jre-modules.sh's jdeps drift check demanded against the
# real M0 backend.jar (see per-module notes below). Extra pinned modules beyond
# what jdeps currently reports are fine — later milestones (POI import/export,
# Timefold solver) are expected to need some of these reflectively; the drift
# check only fails in the other direction (jdeps needs something NOT pinned here).
JLINK_MODULES="java.base,java.compiler,java.desktop,java.instrument,java.logging,java.management,java.naming,java.net.http,java.prefs,java.rmi,java.scripting,java.security.jgss,java.sql,java.sql.rowset,java.xml,java.xml.crypto,jdk.crypto.ec,jdk.jfr,jdk.management,jdk.unsupported"

# --- per-module rationale ---------------------------------------------------
#
# java.base            - always required.
#
# java.compiler        - NOT in the original design-doc list. jdeps demanded it:
#                        Spring's AOT bean-factory code generation
#                        (org.springframework.beans.factory.aot.*,
#                        org.springframework.aot.hint.*) references
#                        javax.lang.model / javax.tools.
#
# java.desktop         - design doc: Apache POI (importer/exporter milestones)
#                        needs AWT classes for shape/drawing support even
#                        headless. Already required today too: spring-beans /
#                        spring-core touch java.beans.* transitively.
#
# java.instrument      - design doc: Spring's load-time class transformation
#                        support (spring-context).
#
# java.logging         - NOT in the original design-doc list (red-team catch,
#                        see docs/adr/003-tauri-jlink-resources.md): embedded
#                        Tomcat's JULI bridge (org.apache.juli) needs
#                        java.util.logging at boot. Omitting it jlinks
#                        successfully but the packaged runtime crashes with a
#                        NoClassDefFoundError at startup — a failure mode a
#                        plain `mvn test` run never exercises, only the
#                        packaged-runtime smoke test.
#
# java.management      - design doc: Spring Boot registers JMX MBeans by
#                        default.
#
# java.naming          - design doc: JNDI lookups pulled in transitively by
#                        Spring/Tomcat.
#
# java.net.http        - design doc: java.net.http.HttpClient (Spring Boot
#                        itself uses it; future outbound calls may too).
#
# java.prefs           - NOT in the original design-doc list. jdeps demanded it
#                        (spring-beans/spring-core -> java.beans.* ->
#                        java.prefs). It is also a hard module-graph
#                        requirement of java.desktop (`java.desktop requires
#                        java.prefs`, unconditional, not `transitive`), so
#                        jlink would silently pull it in even if unlisted —
#                        listed explicitly here for drift-check symmetry.
#
# java.rmi             - NOT in the original design-doc list. jdeps demanded
#                        it when resolving spring-boot / spring-boot-
#                        autoconfigure recursively against the full
#                        BOOT-INF/lib classpath. Root cause: the JDK's
#                        java.management module declares
#                        `uses javax.management.remote.JMXConnectorServerProvider`;
#                        the JDK's own java.management.rmi module provides
#                        that service and itself `requires java.rmi
#                        transitive`. This is a service-binding artifact of
#                        Spring Boot's optional JMX endpoint exposure (java.management
#                        being on the module list), not a direct bytecode call
#                        from our code — but jdeps is right that the module
#                        must be present for that codepath to work if ever
#                        exercised, so it stays pinned.
#
# java.scripting       - NOT in the original design-doc list. jdeps demanded
#                        it: spring-webmvc ships optional script-view support
#                        (org.springframework.web.servlet.view.script.
#                        ScriptTemplateView and friends) that references
#                        javax.script even though the app never registers a
#                        script view.
#
# java.security.jgss   - design doc: Kerberos/GSSAPI codepaths pulled in
#                        transitively by java.naming.
#
# java.sql             - design doc: sqlite-jdbc / Spring JdbcClient
#                        (java.sql.DriverManager etc.), future milestone.
#
# java.sql.rowset      - NOT in the original design-doc list. jdeps demanded it
#                        once M1 added sqlite-jdbc + Flyway (JDBC RowSet API
#                        referenced by the driver/Spring JDBC support). Caught
#                        by the CI drift gate on the first M1 build — exactly
#                        the failure mode the gate exists for.
#
# java.xml             - design doc: POI OOXML (future) + Spring's XML
#                        support. Also a hard module-graph requirement of
#                        java.desktop and java.sql.
#
# java.xml.crypto     - NOT in the original design-doc list. jdeps demanded it
#                        once M3/M4 added Apache POI OOXML (XML signature
#                        support referenced by poi-ooxml). Caught by the CI
#                        drift gate, like java.sql.rowset before it.
#
# jdk.crypto.ec        - design doc: EC/TLS cipher suites. Verified present as
#                        a standalone module in the pinned Temurin 21.0.11+10
#                        jmods (`ls $JAVA_HOME/jmods` lists jdk.crypto.ec.jmod)
#                        — included per the task's "include it only if
#                        present" instruction.
#
# jdk.jfr              - NOT in the original design-doc list. jdeps demanded
#                        it: spring-core ships an optional Flight-Recorder-
#                        backed ApplicationStartup implementation
#                        (org.springframework.core.metrics.jfr.
#                        FlightRecorderApplicationStartup) that references
#                        jdk.jfr.Event directly, even though the app doesn't
#                        enable it.
#
# jdk.management        - NOT in the original design-doc list. jdeps demanded it
#                        once M6a added Timefold Solver Community 1.33.0
#                        (backend/docs/m6a-notes.md): jdeps on the M6a
#                        backend.jar shows BOTH timefold-solver-core-1.33.0.jar
#                        AND its transitive compile dependency
#                        io.micrometer:micrometer-core:1.15.12 (pulled in by
#                        Timefold itself for solver metrics — CPU/move-count
#                        instrumentation — not something this app adds
#                        directly) requiring it; the extended
#                        com.sun.management.* MXBeans (ThreadMXBean/
#                        OperatingSystemMXBean-family) they reference live in
#                        jdk.management, not the base java.management module
#                        already pinned above.
#
# jdk.unsupported      - design doc: sqlite-jdbc (future milestone) uses
#                        sun.misc.Unsafe / sun.nio.ch internals. jdeps also
#                        demands it today (spring-core).
